NC Election

Michael Metzler

November 30, 2018

Load Election Data

This project will be working with the precinct by precinct results of the 11/06/2018 midterm election in the state of North Carolina. These results were obtained from the North Carolina State Board of Elections & Ethics Enforcement website on 11/30/2018 at the following URL: https://dl.ncsbe.gov/ENRS/2018_11_06/results_pct_20181106.zip

NC_Results <- NA
if (file.exists("Data/NC_Results.rds")) {
    NC_Results <- readRDS("Data/NC_Results.rds")
} else {
    if (!file.exists("Data/results_pct_20181106.txt")) {
        curl_download(url = "https://dl.ncsbe.gov/ENRS/2018_11_06/results_pct_20181106.zip", 
            destfile = "Data/results_pct_20181106.zip")
        unzip("Data/results_pct_20181106.zip", exdir = "Data")
    }
    NC_Results <- read_delim("Data/results_pct_20181106.txt", "\t", escape_double = FALSE, 
        trim_ws = TRUE)
    NC_Results %<>% mutate(Choice = if_else(Choice == "" | is.na(Choice), "NONE", 
        as.character(Choice)), `Choice Party` = if_else(`Choice Party` == "" | 
        is.na(`Choice Party`), "NONE", as.character(`Choice Party`)))
    NC_Results %<>% mutate_if(is.numeric, as.integer)
    NC_Results %<>% mutate_if(is.character, factor)
    NC_Results %<>% rename(Early = `One Stop`, Mail = `Absentee by Mail`)
    saveRDS(NC_Results, "Data/NC_Results.rds")
}

District 9

District_9_House <- NC_Results %>% filter(`Contest Name` == "US HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES DISTRICT 09")

District_9_Candidate_By_County <- District_9_House %>% group_by(County, Choice) %>% 
    summarise(`Total Votes` = sum(`Total Votes`), `Election Day` = sum(`Election Day`), 
        Early = sum(Early), Mail = sum(Mail), Provisional = sum(Provisional)) %>% 
    ungroup()

District_9_Total_By_County <- District_9_Candidate_By_County %>% group_by(County) %>% 
    select(-Choice) %>% summarise_all(sum) %>% ungroup()

District_9_By_County <- bind_rows(District_9_Candidate_By_County %>% mutate_at(c("County", 
    "Choice"), as.character), District_9_Total_By_County %>% mutate(County = as.character(County), 
    Choice = "County Total")) %>% arrange(County) %>% mutate(Choice = factor(Choice))

All North Carolina US House Races

NC_US_House_All <- NC_Results %>% filter(str_detect(`Contest Name`, "US HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES")) %>% 
    mutate_at(c("Contest Name", "Choice", "Choice Party"), factor)

NC_US_House_Candidate_By_County <- NC_US_House_All %>% group_by(`Contest Name`, 
    County, Choice, `Choice Party`) %>% summarise(`Total Votes` = sum(`Total Votes`), 
    `Election Day` = sum(`Election Day`), Early = sum(Early), Mail = sum(Mail), 
    Provisional = sum(Provisional)) %>% ungroup()

NC_US_House_Total_By_County <- NC_US_House_Candidate_By_County %>% group_by(`Contest Name`, 
    County) %>% select(-Choice, -`Choice Party`) %>% summarise_all(sum) %>% 
    ungroup()

NC_US_House_By_County <- bind_rows(NC_US_House_Candidate_By_County %>% mutate_at(c("County", 
    "Contest Name", "Choice", "Choice Party"), as.character), NC_US_House_Total_By_County %>% 
    mutate(County = as.character(County), `Contest Name` = as.character(`Contest Name`), 
        Choice = "County Total", `Choice Party` = "County Total")) %>% arrange(`Contest Name`, 
    County) %>% mutate_at(c("County", "Contest Name", "Choice", "Choice Party"), 
    factor)

Set up Colors

red_blue_green <- brewer.pal(3, "Set1")
red <- red_blue_green[1]
blue <- red_blue_green[2]
green <- red_blue_green[3]

District_9_Color_Scale <- scale_fill_manual(name = "Candidate", values = setNames(red_blue_green, 
    c("Mark Harris", "Dan McCready", "Jeff Scott")))

Party_Color_Scale <- scale_fill_manual(name = "Party", values = setNames(red_blue_green, 
    c("REP", "DEM", "OTHER")))

The 9th Congressional District Race

table <- District_9_By_County %>% filter(Choice != "County Total") %>% group_by(Choice) %>% 
    summarise(Votes = sum(`Total Votes`))
ggplot(data = table) + geom_col(aes(x = fct_reorder(Choice, Votes), y = Votes, 
    fill = Choice)) + District_9_Color_Scale + xlab("Candidate") + scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::comma_format()) + 
    ggtitle("Total Votes Cast for Each Candidate in the 9th Congressional District")

table %>% arrange(Votes) %>% mutate(percent = Votes/sum(Votes)) %>% kable(caption = "9th Congressional District Results")

County_Order <- (District_9_Total_By_County %>% arrange(`Total Votes`))$County %>% 
    as.character()

table <- District_9_Candidate_By_County %>% mutate(County = factor(County, levels = County_Order))

ggplot(data = table) + geom_col(aes(x = County, y = `Total Votes`, fill = Choice)) + 
    District_9_Color_Scale + scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::comma_format()) + 
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) + ggtitle("Where Did The Votes Come From?")

ggplot(data = table, aes(x = County, weight = `Total Votes`, fill = Choice)) + 
    District_9_Color_Scale + geom_bar(position = "fill") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, 
    hjust = 1)) + labs(y = "Share of Votes") + geom_hline(yintercept = 0.5) + 
    ggtitle("Who Did Each County Vote For?")

table <- District_9_Total_By_County %>% gather(key = `Vote Type`, value = `Vote Count`, 
    `Election Day`, Early, Mail, Provisional) %>% mutate(County = factor(County, 
    levels = County_Order))
ggplot(table %>% select(-`Total Votes`), aes(x = County, y = `Vote Count`, fill = `Vote Type`), 
    position_stack()) + geom_col() + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, 
    hjust = 1)) + ggtitle("Breakdown of Voting Methods by County")

ggplot(table %>% select(-`Total Votes`), aes(x = County, weight = `Vote Count`, 
    fill = `Vote Type`)) + geom_bar(position = "fill") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, 
    hjust = 1)) + labs(y = "Percentage of Votes Cast") + ggtitle("Proportion of Voting Methods by County")

Difference Between Mail and in Person Ballots

table <- District_9_By_County %>% mutate(`In Person` = `Total Votes` - Mail) %>% 
    gather(key = `Vote Type`, value = `Vote Count`, `Total Votes`, `Election Day`, 
        Early, Mail, Provisional, `In Person`) %>% filter(!Choice == "County Total") %>% 
    filter(`Vote Type` == "Mail" | `Vote Type` == "In Person") %>% group_by(County, 
    `Vote Type`) %>% mutate(`County Total` = sum(`Vote Count`)) %>% mutate(share = `Vote Count`/`County Total`) %>% 
    select(-`Vote Count`, -`County Total`) %>% filter(Choice == "Dan McCready") %>% 
    spread(`Vote Type`, share) %>% ungroup() %>% mutate(County = factor(County, 
    levels = County_Order))

ggplot(data = table) + geom_col(aes(x = County, y = Mail - `In Person`, fill = `In Person` < 
    Mail)) + scale_fill_manual(values = setNames(c(blue, red), c(TRUE, FALSE))) + 
    scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format()) + theme(legend.position = "none", 
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) + labs(y = "Share of Mail In Ballots vs Share of In Person Ballots") + 
    ggtitle("Partisan Lean of Mail In Ballots Relative to Ballots Cast In Person")

State Wide Trends

Overview of US House of Representatives Races

Statewide_shares <- NC_US_House_Candidate_By_County %>% mutate(`Choice Party` = if_else(`Choice Party` == 
    "DEM" | `Choice Party` == "REP", as.character(`Choice Party`), "OTHER")) %>% 
    group_by(`Choice Party`) %>% summarise(`Party Early` = sum(Early), `Party Election Day` = sum(`Election Day`), 
    `Party Mail` = sum(Mail), `Party In Person` = sum(`Total Votes` - Mail), 
    `Party Total` = sum(`Total Votes`)) %>% ungroup() %>% mutate(`Party Election Day Share` = `Party Election Day`/sum(`Party Election Day`), 
    `Party Early Share` = `Party Early`/sum(`Party Early`), `Party Mail Share` = `Party Mail`/sum(`Party Mail`), 
    `Party In Person Share` = `Party In Person`/sum(`Party In Person`), `Party Total Share` = `Party Total`/sum(`Party Total`)) %>% 
    mutate(`Choice Party` = fct_reorder(`Choice Party`, `Party Total`)) %>% 
    arrange(`Party Total`)

Statewide_shares_no_uncontested <- NC_US_House_Candidate_By_County %>% filter(`Contest Name` != 
    "US HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES DISTRICT 03") %>% mutate(`Choice Party` = if_else(`Choice Party` == 
    "DEM" | `Choice Party` == "REP", as.character(`Choice Party`), "OTHER")) %>% 
    group_by(`Choice Party`) %>% summarise(`Party Early` = sum(Early), `Party Election Day` = sum(`Election Day`), 
    `Party Mail` = sum(Mail), `Party In Person` = sum(`Total Votes` - Mail), 
    `Party Total` = sum(`Total Votes`)) %>% ungroup() %>% mutate(`Party Election Day Share` = `Party Election Day`/sum(`Party Election Day`), 
    `Party Early Share` = `Party Early`/sum(`Party Early`), `Party Mail Share` = `Party Mail`/sum(`Party Mail`), 
    `Party In Person Share` = `Party In Person`/sum(`Party In Person`), `Party Total Share` = `Party Total`/sum(`Party Total`)) %>% 
    mutate(`Choice Party` = fct_reorder(`Choice Party`, `Party Total`)) %>% 
    arrange(`Party Total`)

Statewide_shares %>% kable(caption = "All House Races")
Statewide_shares_no_uncontested %>% kable(caption = "Contested House Races")

How Did the Mail in Ballots Compare to Ballots Cast In Person

table3 <- NC_US_House_By_County %>% mutate(`In Person` = `Total Votes` - Mail) %>% 
    gather(key = `Vote Type`, value = `Vote Count`, `Total Votes`, `Election Day`, 
        Early, Mail, Provisional, `In Person`) %>% filter(!Choice == "County Total") %>% 
    group_by(`Contest Name`, County, `Vote Type`) %>% mutate(`County Total` = sum(`Vote Count`)) %>% 
    mutate(share = `Vote Count`/`County Total`) %>% select(-`Vote Count`, -`County Total`) %>% 
    filter(`Choice Party` == "DEM" | `Choice Party` == "REP") %>% spread(`Vote Type`, 
    share) %>% rename_at(vars(-`Contest Name`, -County, -Choice, -`Choice Party`), 
    funs(paste0(., " Share")))

table3 %<>% full_join(NC_US_House_Total_By_County) %>% filter(`Contest Name` != 
    "US HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES DISTRICT 03")

ggplot(data = table3, aes(x = `In Person Share`, y = `Mail Share`, color = `Choice Party`)) + 
    geom_point(data = table3 %>% filter(County == "BLADEN", `Contest Name` == 
        "US HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES DISTRICT 09"), aes(x = `In Person Share`, 
        y = `Mail Share`), color = "yellow", size = 5) + geom_point() + geom_smooth(method = "lm", 
    formula = y ~ x) + geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 
    1), labels = scales::percent_format()) + scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 
    1), labels = scales::percent_format()) + scale_color_manual(values = setNames(c(blue, 
    red), c("DEM", "REP"))) + ggtitle("Partisan Gap Between Mail In Voters and In Person Voters")

ggplot(data = table3, aes(x = `Early Share`, y = `Mail Share`, color = `Choice Party`)) + 
    geom_point(data = table3 %>% filter(County == "BLADEN", `Contest Name` ==

        color = "yellow", size = 5) + geom_point() + geom_smooth(method = "lm", 
    formula = y ~ x) + geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,

    1), labels = scales::percent_format()) + scale_color_manual(values = setNames(c(blue, 
    red), c("DEM", "REP"))) + ggtitle("Partisan Gap Between Mail In Voters and Early Voters")
